I see you had problems with creating scripts that are compatible with SQL Azure. There is an easy way to Generate Scripts that are 100% compatible with SQL Azure using SSMS.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
In SSMS right click on your database and select Tasks &gt; Generate Scripts... When the &quot;Set Scripting Options&quot; dialog appears click the &quot;Advanced&quot; button and then for &quot;Script for the database engine type&quot; select &quot;SQL Azure Database&quot;.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The following link opens a blog post that shows how it is done: http://bit.ly/kh9cC6&lt;br /&gt;

